The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum-average-length prefix-free set of codewords over an alphabet of nonuniform letter costs. This problem is closely related to information theory and coding theory, which are covered by the cs.IT sub-category. The paper also introduces new structural properties of such codes, which are related to data structures and algorithms, covered by the cs.DS sub-category. The problem of finding an optimal $r$-ary search tree with $n$ leaves is a classic problem in computer science, covered by the cs.DM sub-category. The paper also discusses the time complexity of the algorithm, which is related to computational complexity, covered by the cs.CC sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which are related to machine learning and statistics, covered by the cs.LG sub-category.
